<whmacros>
<whdoc>
The session variable "inSpeed" is defined based on surfer input via radio button--see below.
This determines the name of the directory from which the images are taken.
The color images are considered acceptable for fast connections, and the black and white 
images are for slow connections.
</whdoc>
mcImgDir=(~mcSiteRoot~)demos/whOptions/(~inSpeed~)/
</whmacros>

<whdroplet name="drDemoSpeedbarForbw" show="no">
(~JUMP|pgWebHubTimes|WH Times~) | (~JUMP|pgNews|RSS Example~)
</whdroplet>

<whpage pageid="pgEnterBW" remap="(apphttp)" desc="Bandwidth Picker">
<whdoc>
The surfer clicks a radio button to specify a fast or slow connection.
Clicking this radio button sets the session variable named "inSpeed" to either "fast" or "slow".
</whdoc>
<whprep>
(~NOTASSIGNED|inSpeed|(~SET|inSpeed=Fast~)~) <!---Default the speed setting to fast.-->
</whprep>
<whoutput>
(~mcdoctypehtml~)
<html>
<head>
(~drHead~)
</head>
<body>
(~drPageBegin~)
<div id="whdemopagecontent">
<div class="dcenter">

<form method="post" action="(~ACTION|BW:pgWebHubTimes~)">

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
	<tr>
		<td align="center" valign="middle">
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td align="center" valign="middle">
<span style="font-size:2em;color:red">This site is graphics-intensive.</span><br />
<span style="font-size:2em;">Please specify your preferred bandwidth:</span>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td align="center" valign="middle">
<br /><br />

(~INPUTRADIO|inSpeed,slow~) Slow Modem  <!---Let the visitor override the setting. -->
(~INPUTRADIO|inSpeed,fast~) Fast Connection
<br /><br />
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td align="center" valign="middle">(~inputsubmit|submit,Proceed~)
		</td>
	</tr>
</table>
</form>

</div>
<br /><br />
(~whDemoLongDescBW~)
</div>  <!--- demopagecontent -->
(~drPageEnd~)
</body></html>
</whoutput>
</whpage>


